In addition to insurance, it goes out for $15 a day.
And the rental of a bicycle will go out for 15 shequels a day.
Tickets to the museums cost an average of 30 shéquels.
Israel in figures
In 2012, more than three million tourists from around the world visited Israel.
Most of those who came to tour the country and rest were citizens of the U.S., Russia, France, Germany, Italy, the United Kingdom and Ukraine.
The Promised Land, from January to October 2012, was visited by 118.8 thousand Ukrainian tourists, an amount that exceeds by 51% the same index of 2010, before the cancellation of the visa regime on February 9, 2011.
