Šimon Ornest: In our concerts we want to accumulate positive energy
It is said that in just under a month the end of the world will come, what do you think about it?
It's just one of many other alarmist news that we like to grab on.
The music group The Tap Tap we like to make jokes about this and we like to say that we are the only music group in the world that manages to gather enough positive energy to postpone the end of the world or to avoid it.
In addition, in December you organize a really original project: three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you explain it to our readers?
It is a state charity event that we have been planning for two years.
We decided to take advantage of the marketing potential that has the end of the Mayan calendar enunciated for December 21 at 11:10 in the morning.
The day before, on December 20 at 21 hours, we will organize 3 simultaneous concerts in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will end at about the same time that the Mayan calendar ends on Kiribati Island, in the Pacific Ocean, 12 hours ahead of our time zone.
Who came up with this idea?
Initially it was my idea, then we forged the project all together with our designer Honza Augusta.
In addition to wanting to gather enough positive energy and avoiding the end of the world, we also want to reflect, together with society, on the state in which we will leave the world to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar we have also created a unique collection of items: boots, t-shirts, bags and original keychains against the end of the world that can be purchased at www.e-tap.cz, another way to support us.
The group The Tap Tap, along with other performers, also sang the so-called anthem against the end of the world, which is entitled "End of the World, Canceled".
Nowadays it is very popular on YouTube, can you hear in the charity concerts?
Of course, yes, and it will be just the last, well, as long as everything goes well and the world does not end...
She will be sung by all performers at the same time at the three concerts.
The anthems will link together simultaneously thanks to the special live broadcast on Czech Television.
Tomáš Hanák has written the lyrics of this song and plays the starring role of Jesus in the video clip, where Xindl X also sings...
How did this collaboration come about?
We work together even with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, apart from organizing many charity events and concerts...
We make every effort to participate in this project.
It has been shown that most of them are interested in and have fun working with us.
What will the money raised in concerts against the end of the world go to?
To equipment for the educational center without barriers Studeo, which we carry out in its sixth consecutive year with the civil association Tap in Jedličkův ústav.
The students of the school of Jedličkův ústav regularly receive the visit of teachers with whom they perform fun and interesting activities.
Students do not have sufficient financial means to pay teachers and we make an effort to make it possible.
Within the framework of the completion of the works in Jedličkův ústav, there will be an independent building to which we will move with this project.
At each concert, several groups and performers perform.
What are the selection criteria?
We try to develop a program that is attractive to all generations, including children.
For example, in Prague will perform Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý.
For more detailed information, you can consult www.kpks.cz.
Do you plan any other similar "spectacular action" in the future?
In May we will perform for the first time at the Pražské jaro festival, so here we will surely prepare an attractive program with interesting guests.
Next year we would also like to play at the Bohemian National Hall in New York and me, personally, taking advantage of the fact that we are in the United States, I would like to complete it with performances in Washington and Chicago.
Your plans abroad are not exactly minimalist, so far you have acted for example in Madrid, Brussels, London or Moscow.
The Tap Tap is, however, a group of people with disabilities.
What is the logistics and organization of these trips?
It's not that hard how it may seem at first sight.
There are five members in electric wheelchair, the chairs must travel in the luggage compartment and we also carry a lot of weight, the boxes with the instruments...
However, so far we have managed well. ČSA and British Airways were perfectly prepared, which never ceases to surprise me.
Even in Moscow, where we have recently returned from, everything came out without problems.
Thanks to the trips abroad you can compare the different attitudes of society towards the disabled and other aspects.
What have you met so far?
In Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities, everything works better than here; in Russia we have witnessed that, in the east, there is still a long way to go.
Unlike Prague, Moscow is full of barriers, there it remains uncommon for a person to travel alone through the city center in an electric wheelchair.
Something as common as, for example, giving preference to someone in a wheelchair by elevator, there is not.
Fortunately, a civil partnership has been created that strives to thematicize the problems of persons with disabilities.
In what aspects should we take an example from more developed countries?
There are many aspects in which we go behind...
But it is important to mention that perfecting and improving the situation always depends on the people it directly affects.
In London and Madrid it is very normal for people with a serious disability to move on their own in public and be able to go to the service, to the museum, wherever they want...
But it is not very common for a large number of people with disabilities to participate in social life actively, in this regard, with The Tap Tap we are a little ahead!
A respectful or barrier-free society is one thing, but when the time comes when eminent athletes, artists, actors, politicians or lawyers arise, it will begin to change everything really.
So far, they are isolated cases of people who have great willpower.
The Tap Tap group is currently very popular, but if we look a few years ago, what led you to form the group in 1998?
I entered as an educator at Jedličkův ústav, where I had many young people around me who wanted to devote themselves to something.
And since I am a musician, I play, among others, the saxophone, I founded an amateur group with a co-worker.
And over time, as our moderator Láďa Angelovič says, we left a little of our hands (laughs).
However, popularity did not come until the last few years, or am I wrong?
It is true that we were quite helped by connecting with famous singers and also actively working to promote the group.
We conclude that the work that is not seen is as if it does not exist.
Thanks to the aid of the European Union, we can also afford quality teachers, equipment, etc.
Did you intend to go this far with The Tap Tap?
From the beginning I saw the potential that there was, that something can be done otherwise.
The show business is full of things that look like each other.
It is logical, in its own way, everything new is cautiously welcomed and takes a long time to accept.
There are few extraordinary things, but I dare say that The Tap Tap is one of them.
The impression of someone who sees us for the first time is clearly compassion, it is a natural reaction...
But compassion is totally superfluous because people with disabilities are not abandoned beings who suffer and of whom we must have compassion.
There are people who are able to live a full life and develop, with the condition, of course, that they have the necessary means.
I always say that if something goes well for people with disabilities, then it is not only a step forward for them, but for the whole society.
Did you help the fact that you are a demanding boss, as many people describe you?
If we want to do quality work, we have to be rigorous in many respects and demand some discipline.
I think it's completely normal.
Some people arrive with a romantic vision and their heads in the clouds and when they learn that they have to go two days to rehearse, go to the preparatory test and spend a lot of time traveling and at concerts, the initial euphoria abandons them quickly.
But that’s how it works everywhere, in every group that wants to work and get something.
Currently, The Tap Tap has twenty members.
How many of them were already in the early 1998 year?
Only one: Láďa Angelovič.
We are an open group, people come in and out, you can’t help.
Anyone who has the will and desire will always find the doors open
